card.name: Piety
card.text: Whenever you cast a white spell, you gain X life, where X is 1 plus the number of times you've gained life this turn. At the beginning of each end step, if you have at least 20 life more than your starting life total, create a 4/4 white Angel creature token with flying.

card.name: Chronomancy
card.text: You may cast blue spells as though they had flash. They can't be countered. Whenever you cast a spell, untap target permanent if its your turn. Otherwise, tap target permanent.

card.name: Antipathy
card.text: Whenever you cast a spell, Antipathy deals 1 damage to each opponent. It deals 2 damage instead if that spell was red. As long as an opponent has 10 or less life, creatures you control gain +1/+0 and have haste.

card.name: Loyalty
card.text: Whenever you cast a green spell, proliferate. Whenever you activate an ability of a planeswalker or attack, put a +1/+1 counter or a loyalty counter on target permanent.

card.name: Chicanery
card.text: Whenever you cast a black spell you own, exile the top card of each opponent's library. You may play those cards as long as they remain exiled, and you may spend mana as though it was mana of any color to do so. At the beginning of your end step, each opponent loses life equal to the number of permanents you control that you don't own.

card.name: Chiresian Consort Throne

card.name: The Fate Engine
card.text: Whenever you cast a spell, create a 0/0 colorless Army creature token, then put a +1/+1 counter on each Army you control. Once on each of your turn, you may cast a spell with mana value 3 or less without paying its mana cost.

card.text: You may remove X counters from a black planeswalker you control rather than pay this spell's mana cost. Exile the top X cards of each opponent's library. As long as those cards remained exiled, you may play lands and cast spells from among them during your turn, and mana of any type can be spent to play them.
